result.execSummary:
Tao Vang was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Tao Vang was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Letter to Governor w/copy of complaints, waiver of extradition and warrant papers

11:16 AM Defendant Tao Vang in court. Attorney (Atty) Taylor Soule is present. Prosecuting Assistant District Attorney (ADA) Brian J Pfeil appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Interpreter Lee Yang is sworn in to interpret.  Atty Soule request the Court to allow her to evaluate the Defendant to determine if he is eligible for representation. Court requests the interpreter to work with the public defender Atty Soule to intrepret.
Court clears the Courtroom at this time. 11:20 am
11:40 AM Court back in session.  Atty Soule states that the Defendant is not eligible for public defender representation.
Court reads the complaint with the Minnesota warrant information to the Defendant and is interpreted by Interperter Yang. 
Court informs Defendant of Rights of Accused as to the issuance and service of a warrant of extradition and action for habeas corpus.
Court questions the Defendant if he waives his rights and requests to be returned to Minnesota.
Defendant wishes to be sent back to Minnesota.
Court determines that the Defendant has freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waived his rights.
ADA Pfeil reads the waiver and consent form and is interpreted to the Defendant.

BY THE COURT:
Defendant consents to be returned to the demanding state.
Defendant is willing to waive his right to the habeas action.
Defendant signed the waiver of extradition as of today's date and will be provided a copy of the form.
Defendant will be returned to Minnesota.
A Warrant of Arrest issued by the Judge Laura Marie Thomas, District Court Judge for Hennepin County, Minnesota.
